d. 	General Services Officer determine (i) all the unserviceable PPEs beyond economic repair and have a separate report thereof, and (ii) items for reclassification to inventory accounts for the correct reporting of the PPEs in the inventory report.

1.10	 We recommended that the:
Local Chief Executive create the (a) appraisal committee for the determination of the current market  value of the titled parcels of land for the recording thereof in the books of the Municipality;  and (b) inventory committee to complete the conduct of physical inventory of PPE to determine the actual existence of all assets owned by the Municipality;
General Services Officer coordinate with the Municipal Assessor to ascertain the status of other parcels of land owned by the Municipality with titling issues and facilitate the titling thereof in the name of the Municipality of Guagua;
General Services Officer and the Municipal Accountant (i) maintain complete  Property Cards and PPE Ledger Cards , respectively, for all the properties of the Municipality; (ii) initiate the necessary reconciliation of the  accounting records of the PPE accounts balances with the physical inventory report; and (iii) reclassify the PPE items in the RCPPCE to ascertain the actual amount of each PPE account; and
Municipal Accountant determine the remaining useful life of the infrastructure assets for the provision of accumulated depreciation.

Members of the MDRRMC organize the functional organization of the ICS, the required training and resource management which include the personnel, teams, equipment, and other facilities available during emergencies, as a perfect tool in responding to all types of hazards most particularly in an on-scene emergency situations and calamities such as flooding;

Municipal Accountant, along with the other offices/officials concerned, comply with the submission of the lacking documents/information as discussed above, for the evaluation of the Audit Team and subsequent audit action; and

Municipal Mayor and MDRRMO continue being generally compliant with the minimum requirements on disaster preparedness and in the allocation and utilization of the LDRRMF for calamity/disaster-related expenses.

We recommended that the


Members of the Municipal Local School Board  allocate the SEF budget only for eligible and priority program, projects and activities allowed by the law and encourage schools to make use of the DepEd’s funds for their regular operations;  



Members of the Municipal Local School Board and Municipal Budget Officer ensure that all charges in the SEF are within  adherence to the provisions of R.A. 5447, Section 100 and 272, RA 7160 and DepEd-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 01, s. 2017 dated January 19, 2017 in the preparation of the CY 2018 SEF budget and in the utilization of the CY 2017 Local School Board Fund;

Members of the Municipal Local School Board thru the Municipal  Treasurer, ensure that all expenses are paid through checks except for petty expenditures to avoid the possible misuse of government funds;


Members of the Municipal Local School Board thru the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer, allow only the grant of cash advances for time-bound activities to duly appointed or designated disbursing officers of the Municipality; and


Municipal Budget Officer ensure that the OBR bear the signature of the concerned District Supervisor before recording the obligation.

